/*!
\page mathfunctions_idiv IDIV Integer Division Operation

<p>
Section: \ref sec_mathfunctions "Mathematical Functions"
\section Usage
Computes the integer division of two arrays.  The syntax for its use is
\verbatim
   y = idiv(a,b)
\endverbatim
where <tt>a</tt> and <tt>b</tt> are arrays or scalars.  The effect of the <tt>idiv</tt>
is to compute the integer division of <tt>b</tt> into <tt>a</tt>.
\section Example
The following examples show some uses of <tt>idiv</tt>
arrays.

